<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.65.30" />

<fw type="curatorial">30</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine Street<lb/>
Lincoln, Nebraska 6<del>5</del><add>8</add>505<lb/>
May 24, 1973
</dateline>

<address>
<addrLine>Mr. Terrence O'Neill</addrLine>
<addrLine>521 N. Central</addrLine>
<addrLine>St. Louis, Missouri 63130</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>Dear Terry O'Neill:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I want you to know that I deeply appreciate your beautiful letter of May 5, 1973. I am glad to know that I do not seem "far away or long ago" to you. I am neither, as you know, and at the present moment I feel very close to you, indeed.</p>

<p>Your comment on the poem "Ghostly Brother" tells me a great deal about you, and it is good to know.</p>

<p>I hope we may meet some time.</p>

<p>Do you know that United Artists is bringing out some albums of my work? The first is now being prepared and I think will be out in July. We worked on the records for a period of eight weeks and they are now working on the albums in Hollywood.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Thanks and best wishes, your friend</salute>


<signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>

<note>JGN:nh</note>
</closer>

</div1>
</body>

